cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving end-to-end neural machine translation using bidirectional attention-based models. The paper focuses on the alignment of words between source and target languages, which is a key aspect of natural language translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a joint training approach that encourages two complementary models to agree on word alignment matrices, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses neural networks, which could place it in categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
